**Setting up the problem:**
- Y ~ b(n, 0.25), so E[Y] = np = 500(0.25) = 125
- Var(Y) = np(1-p) = 500(0.25)(0.75) = 93.75
- We want P(|Y/n - 0.25| < 0.05)

**Rewriting the inequality:**
|Y/n - 0.25| < 0.05 is equivalent to |Y - 0.25n| < 0.05n

With n = 500:
